Class TransitionEffectTrait<State,​Delta>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nasa.jpl.ammos.mpsa.aerie.merlinsdk.effects.traits.TransitionEffectTrait<State,​Delta>
  • Type Parameters:
    State - The type of states to be traversed.
    Delta - The type of differences between states.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    EffectTrait<Transition<State,​Delta>>
    public class TransitionEffectTrait<State,​Delta>
extends Object
implements EffectTrait<Transition<State,​Delta>>
    An effect algebra over automata transition functions. Transition functions model a change from a given input state to some output state via some delta effect. We may define sequential composition of transition functions by applying one transition to the state produced from another, and concurrent composition as the composition of the deltas produced by applying both transitions to the same input. This is useful when modeling events as processes that depend on the results from previous effects.
    See Also:
    EffectTrait, Transition, Action
